cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT

This paper proposes a novel interference coordination scheme for future cellular networks, which involves mathematical programming, game theory, and distributed scheduling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and optimization, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses resource allocation and scheduling, which are relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
